elry piece. The soldering is done traditionally by puffing fire out of pipes onto the gold pieces and combining them into one solid piece, such as an earring or a necklace.\n\nThe black residue on the jewelry piece after the soldering process is cleaned using mild chemicals and then dried. After this, the piece is handed over to the gem setter. In gem setting, first the lac is heated and poured into the creek, which is supposed to hold the gem. Meanwhile the gem or stone that has to be encrusted is prepared. A gold or silver foil is fixed to the back of the gem to make it gleam. The gemstones are now placed into the creeks or holders.\n\nIn the final step, the bits of 24 carat gold foils or kundan are set into the sides of the gemstones till they grip on tightly. In the Meenakari process, which is intricate and laborious, enamel colors are added to the jewelry piece through an engraving and fusing technique.\n\nEvery Indian bride dreams of wearing a one-of-a-kind Kundan Meena jewelry set these days. After exquisite Kundan Meena pieces worn by Aishwarya Rai in the Bollywood epic Jodha Akbar caught the publics fancy, many jewelry showrooms in India have seen a rise in sales of Kundan Meena jewelry. Traditional handcrafted jewelry such as Kundan Meena has been cherished for centuries in India and is now finding popularity world over.","Making of Kundan Meena Jewelry","This writeup tells in details about one of the very popular and traditional jewelry art in India","inherit","open","open","","52-revision-15","","","2011-01-28 13:38:07","2011-01-28 13:38:07","","52","http://www.nethaat.com/blog/?p=69","0","revision","","0");
