INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("118","1","2011-02-20 06:19:15","2011-02-20 06:19:15"," \n\nIndian clothing has always been known for its elegance and aesthetics. To begin with, fashion in India was confined to the traditional sari, which was a complex and difficult garment for the West to duplicate. But recent years have seen young designers blending the traditional with the modern and creating stunning one-of-a-kind designs. Indian fashion has carved a niche for itself on the international stage. Here are some of Indias well known designers and their unique styles.\n\n <strong>Ritu Beri</strong>\n\nBeris designs are effervescent and epitomize the spirit of the modern Indian woman. In line with the needs of todays career oriented woman, Beris designs are tailored to be comfortable and chic while keeping the formal appearance intact. In her own words, Beri wants every girl who wears her creations to be confident in her own ability to set fashion trends. With her designs extremely popular in the US, Paris and London, Ritu Beri has come a long way from her early days as one of the first graduates of the National Institute of Fashion Technology.\n\n <strong>Rohit Bal</strong>\n\nAs the most sought after celebrity fashion designer, Rohit Bal has had success clothing both Bollywood beauties and Indian fashionistas. His skill with fabric has been acknowledged by the Time magazine which called him The Master of Fabric and Fantasy\', a great honor for an Indian designer. His style is deliberately simple yet makes a definite statement. Bal draws from tradition for inspiration. His designs are appreciated for their aesthetics, intricacies and attention to detail. Each of his pieces has an unmatched look and feel.\n\n<strong>Tarun Tahiliani</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>Tahilianis designs evoke the age old charm of Indian heritage although the garments themselves are modern and contemporary. This Fashion Institute of Technology  graduates creations are high on elegance. Tarun Tahilianis Ensemble range has changed the way the modern Indian fashion is interpreted with its beautiful and unique craftsmanship.\n\n <strong>Ritu Kumar</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>Ritu Kumars tryst with ancient traditional weaving and Indian dyeing arts continues to this day. Her exquisite bridal collection is considered to be the best in India. Kumars traditional yet trendy designs have been appreciated by fashion connoisseurs all over the world, including the late Princess Diana. Her fusion of Indian style of embroidery and embellishment with western attire has received enthusiastic response around the globe.\n\n<strong>Manish Malhotra</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>The blue eyed boy of Bollywood, Malhotra has been the favorite designer for scores of leading ladies of movies for many years. He is credited with being the first designer to craft a special look for a films subject. His style transcends international borders as is evident from his global admirers like Naomi Campbell and the late Michael Jackson. Malhotra has a unique perspective on style. He believes that any garment can be made uber cool irrespective of whether it has been designed for high fashion or as casual clothing.\n\n A number of up-and-coming Indian designers are making their mark on the international fashion scene. Celebrity endorsements have also brought the designers into the spotlight. Many Indian designers are also opening their signature boutiques in India and abroad in an effort to become more accessible to the common man.","Design Styles of Top Indian Fashion Designers","","inherit","open","open","","111-revision-2","","","2011-02-20 06:19:15","2011-02-20 06:19:15","","111","http://www.nethaat.com/blog/?p=118","0","revision","","0");
